# Upgrade api_express — Implementation Plan

## Context

The `api_express/` directory contains a partially completed Express.js API (~2018) that served portfolio data from MariaDB. It was superseded by the local JSON approach but the user has restored its source code and wants to upgrade it to modern Node.js and complete the endpoints to match what `www/` needs.

**Key discovery:** The DB does not contain media data in the shape the frontend needs. `has_archive`, `is_flash`, `is_dark_background` flags and image dimensions (`width`, `height`) don't exist in the DB — they came from a separate `data.json` file that was merged into `portfolio.json` during the migration. The API will serve entry metadata only; media data stays in `portfolio.json` at build time.

---

## Decisions

- **Data source:** MariaDB on the NAS
- **Runtime:** Node 22, native ESM (no Babel, no TypeScript)
- **Legacy dirs:** Keep `_sequelizejs/`, `buildtools/`, `tools/`, `autorun/` as reference
- **Deployment:** Simple `npm start` — no Docker for now
- **Media data:** Not served by the API (DB lacks the required fields)

---

## API Endpoints (matching www service layer)

| Endpoint | Matches service function | Response shape |
|---|---|---|
| `GET /api/categories` | `fetchAvailableCategoriesService()` | `[{ category_id, category_name, category_label, category_description, is_active }]` |
| `GET /api/categories/active` | `fetchAllActiveCategoriesByYearService()` | `{ "2018": { "web": true }, "allyears": { ... } }` |
| `GET /api/categories/:categoryId/:yearId` | `fetchCategoryItemsService()` | `{ entries: [...], years: [...], active_categories: {...} }` |
| `GET /api/item/:entryId` | `fetchItemService()` | `{ id, client_id, entry_id, client_label, category, title, description, responsibilities, year, is_responsive, is_summary, is_featured, affiliation, affiliation_url, technologies, frameworks, territories, platforms }` |

Archive JSON (`fetchArchiveItemService`) continues to be served as static files from `www/public/` — no API endpoint needed.

